2016, the title of tallest building in Singapore is held by [[Tanjong Pagar Centre]].\n\nBuildings with this sign (*) indicate that they have been demolished.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Name\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Image\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Street address\n! Years as tallest\n! Height (m)\n! Height (ft)\n! Floors\n! Coordinates\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Reference\n|-\n| [[Cathay Building]]\n|[[File:The Cathay 3, Jan 06.JPG|80px|alt=Rounded building with two visibile facades; the lower floors have a concrete exterior with grooved, triangular niches and round, protruding edges. The uppermost floors, slightly less prominent, have a glass exterior.]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2 Handy Road\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1939\u20131954\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 70\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 230\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 17\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{coord|1|17|57.5|N|103|50|51.5|E}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"CATHAY emp\"/>\n|-\n| [[Asia Insurance Building]]\n|[[File:Asia Insurance Building, Dec 05.JPG|80px|alt= Beige rectangular building, 20 storeys and at 87 metres tall, with newer taller skyscrapers seen in the background.]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2 Finlayson Green\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1954\u20131971\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 87\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 285\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{coord|1|16|55|N|103|51|05|E}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"AIB\">{{cite web | publisher = National Library of Singapore | title = Asia Insurance Building | url = http://infopedia.nl.sg/articles/SIP_592_2005-01-17.html | accessdate = 19 July 2010 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070704201241/http://infopedia.nlb.gov.sg/articles/SIP_592_2005-01-17.html | archivedate = 4 July 2007 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Shaw House and Centre|Shaw Centre]]\n|[[File:Shawctr.JPG|80px|alt=Box-like buildin